post_text: Due to the increase in COVID-19 cases, to ensure the safety of our students, staff, families and community, Distance Learning will continue for the 1st quarter. We want our students in school for face-to-face learning and will reevaluate in September to see if we can begin a hybrid model 2nd quarter, or possibly 2nd semester. Students remain our top priority and we will do everything possible to protect them, while maintaining our dedication to every student graduating ready for college, career ... and life. #theCVway #StudentsFirst #DistanceLearning

NBC 4 News - Black History Month, Defying The Odds

Kinecta
February 28 at 1:45 PM ¬∑

As part of our commitment to the advancement and strengthening of the communities we serve, we hosted our 2nd annual Defying the Odds Black History Month Event. It addressed the unique challenges that African-American boys face while transitioning from high school to college or into full-time employment. Participants had access to a panel discussion composed of African-American professionals who shared stories about overcoming adversity to achieve professional success. Hats off to Manhattan Beach Police Department Chief, Derrick Abel, for his amazing and inspiring keynote speech! Check out the event's video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A00jNgoytks Mira Costa High School Centinela Valley Union High School District Compton Unified School District NBC LA

Benefits
-$252 monthly stipend
-Free medical, dential, vision, and life insurance benefits

Requirements to apply for the Board Vacancy
-At least be 18 years of age
-U.S. Citizen
-Registered Voter
-Resident of Area 5 LawndaleSD.net/map
Why you should attend the Filling a Board Vacancy Information Session on October 24th at 9:00 AM or 5:00 PM
-You believe in ensuring equal opportunity for all students -Would like to learn about the role of a Board Member -Interested in the current appointment process
-If you do not live in area 5, but are interested in the November 2020 election process

The application is available online (link in profile), in the district office, or by emailing Marina_Sandoval@LawndaleSD.net. We look forward to seeing you on Thursday, October 24th at 9:00 AM or 5:00 PM in the District Office located at 4161 W. 147th Street, Lawndale, CA 90260. Application deadline is Friday, October 25th by 4:00 PM.

post_text: So proud of our 3 Lawndale High School #MESA students who completed the CSULB - National Summer Transportation Institute and attended the National Flight Academy, a one-week immersive learning experience for students interested in #STEM. The program is housed at the US Naval Air Station in Pensacola, Florida. Students were taught and exposed to aerodynamics, navigation, communications, and other disciplines in flight. Our students collaborated with students from all over the country to to use factors such as altitude, distance, and fuel to complete their tasks. Students rotated between being pilots in the flight simulator and communications. Thank you, South Bay Workforce Investment Board - SBWIB, for providing our students such an amazing opportunity! #theCVway #StudentsFirst #Learn

post_text: 23 dedicated Hawthorne High School of Manufacturing & Engineering students graduated from the South Bay Workforce Investment Board - SBWIB Aero-Flex Pre-Apprenticeship Program today. They earned certificates in Track 1 Blueprint For Success, Track 2 SME Tooling University, and Track 3 work-experience as an apprentice in labs. post_text: Three lucky Lawndale High School students were chosen to participate in the CSULB - National Summer Transportation Institute, thanks to the South Bay Workforce Investment Board - SBWIB. Last weekend, our students, along with 4 Inglewood SD students, went to Flabob Airport in Riverside as a culmination of the two-week #STEM and transportation industry program. During their 3 days at the airport, they learned all about airplanes and how to fly them. Each student flew around an adjacent mountain for 20-30 minutes with an instructor. They will complete the program next weekend with a trip to NASA - National Aeronautics and Space Administration in Florida. #theCVway #StudentsFirst #Learn
